aim.body:
This Tender Evaluation and Probity Plan (TEPP) is the planning and control document in conducting the evaluation of Tenders received in response to the RFT. The TEPP sets out:
• the processes and principles to be followed when evaluating Tenders;
• individual's responsibilities;
• the evaluation schedule;
• reporting requirements.
The tenderers shall provide all necessary information as per the context provided, including manufacturer's rated performance data for the Chiller offered, full dimensional details in the form of certified drawings, weights, electrical requirements, wiring diagrams, evidence of conformance with AS1677.2 and AS1210, accessories and features provided with the Chiller offered, details of facilities and services required for the Chiller offered, and any other associated works not specifically mentioned in this scope of works to form a complete and operating system.
